## Mandatory Working Rules
- If confidence is below 90%, pause and ask 1-3 precise clarifying questions.
- Make smallest correct change first; avoid unnecessary scope.
- For behavior changes, add/update targeted tests.
- For Tier B/C projects, maintain `docs/MASTER_TRACEABILITY_TABLE.md` and ensure each active Path ID has smoke/contract coverage (`Automated`, `Manual`, or `N/A` with rationale).
- Update docs in the same change when behavior, commands, paths, or structure changes.
- Regenerate AI context map: `[AI_CONTEXT_COMMAND]`.
- Run verify gate before handoff: `[VERIFY_COMMAND]`.

## File Size and Modularity Rules
- Soft target: keep new files <= 400 lines.
- Hard trigger: refactor when any source file > 500 lines.
- Keep modules cohesive and dependency direction clear.

